<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <!--
        Sauce Bunny — Hardened Runtime entitlements for notarization.

        Distribution model: self-hosted notarized DMG (NOT Mac App
        Store). The App Sandbox keys (com.apple.security.app-sandbox,
        com.apple.security.files.user-selected.read-write, etc.) are
        intentionally NOT set — they're App-Store-only requirements
        that would break our sidecar-spawning architecture for no
        gain on the .dmg path.

        See DISTRIBUTION.md for the full reasoning + release flow.

        Principle: grant the minimum the app actually needs. Each
        entitlement here loosens a Hardened Runtime restriction that
        would otherwise block a real runtime behaviour.
    -->

    <!--
        Required: whisper.cpp accelerates inference via Metal compute
        kernels. Metal shaders are technically JIT-compiled at first
        use; without allow-jit, the hardened runtime blocks the
        writable-executable memory pages Metal needs.
        Also covers WKWebView's JavaScript JIT.
    -->
    <key>com.apple.security.cs.allow-jit</key>
    <true/>

    <!--
        Required: yt-dlp ships as a PyInstaller bundle. At startup it
        self-extracts the Python interpreter + bundled dylibs into a
        randomised /tmp directory and dlopen()s them from there. Those
        dylibs are NOT code-signed by our Developer ID (PyInstaller
        signs them with its own at build time), so the hardened
        runtime's default library-validation check blocks the load.
        This entitlement allows that pattern.
    -->
    <key>com.apple.security.cs.disable-library-validation</key>
    <true/>

    <!--
        Allowed by default for hardened runtime + Developer ID
        distribution, but we declare it explicitly so a reviewer can
        see exactly what surface this app touches. The app makes
        network calls only for: user-initiated yt-dlp downloads,
        Whisper model downloads from HuggingFace mirrors, and the
        diarizer model fetch on first run.
    -->
    <key>com.apple.security.network.client</key>
    <true/>

    <!--
        Required: the app reads/writes the user's Documents directory
        for the transcript library (~/Documents/Sauce Bunny/Transcripts/).
        Not actually enforced by hardened runtime (this is an App
        Sandbox key) but harmless to declare and useful as future-
        proofing if Apple ever adds Documents access prompts outside
        the sandbox.
    -->
    <!-- NOTE: intentionally NOT declaring com.apple.security.app-sandbox
         here. We are NOT a sandboxed app. -->
</dict>
</plist>
